description: From Middle English overreden, from Old English oferrǣdan (“to read over; read through; consider”), equivalent to over- +‎ read.

adjectives.description: overread (comparative more overread, superlative most overread)

verbs.description: overread (third-person singular simple present overreads, present participle overreading, simple past and past participle overread)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To read over, or peruse. [10th–19th c.]
(transitive) To interpret something to a greater degree, or in a more positive way, than appropriate; read too in-depth; overinterpret; overanalyze.
examples: To overread Plath's houses is to transform these biographical documents into spatial ones.

entries.meaning: To read too much or excessively.
